Definition: In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element.

Positive Examples.explanation: The element with the largest absolute value is -11. This is a good example.
-200 and 200 have the same absolute value and the positive element, 200, was returned. This is a good example.

Negative Examples.explanation: The element 10 has a larger absolute value than 9.9. This is a bad example.
The element -15 has the largest absolute value but the absolute value was returned. The element itself, not the absolute value should be returned. This is a bad example.
The largest value, 1, was returned but the largest absolute value needs to be returned. This is a bad example.
